{"id":680414,"date":"2025-05-12T16:50:30","date_gmt":"2025-05-12T11:20:30","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/?p=680414"},"modified":"2025-11-24T18:36:26","modified_gmt":"2025-11-24T13:06:26","slug":"ba-first-year-subjects","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/blogs\/complete-list-of-ba-subjects","title":{"rendered":"Guide to BA Degree Courses: Subject List, Specializations &amp; Opportunities"},"content":{"rendered":"<div id=\"ez-toc-container\" class=\"ez-toc-v2_0_82_2 counter-hierarchy ez-toc-counter ez-toc-grey ez-toc-container-direction\">\n<div class=\"ez-toc-title-container\">\n<p class=\"ez-toc-title\" style=\"cursor:inherit\">Table of Contents<\/p>\n<span class=\"ez-toc-title-toggle\"><a href=\"#\" class=\"ez-toc-pull-right ez-toc-btn ez-toc-btn-xs ez-toc-btn-default ez-toc-toggle\" aria-label=\"Toggle Table of Content\"><span class=\"ez-toc-js-icon-con\"><span class=\"\"><span class=\"eztoc-hide\" style=\"display:none;\">Toggle<\/span><span class=\"ez-toc-icon-toggle-span\"><svg style=\"fill: #999;color:#999\" xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" class=\"list-377408\" width=\"20px\" height=\"20px\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\"><path d=\"M6 6H4v2h2V6zm14 0H8v2h12V6zM4 11h2v2H4v-2zm16 0H8v2h12v-2zM4 16h2v2H4v-2zm16 0H8v2h12v-2z\" fill=\"currentColor\"><\/path><\/svg><svg style=\"fill: #999;color:#999\" class=\"arrow-unsorted-368013\" xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" width=\"10px\" height=\"10px\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" version=\"1.2\" baseProfile=\"tiny\"><path d=\"M18.2 9.3l-6.2-6.3-6.2 6.3c-.2.2-.3.4-.3.7s.1.5.3.7c.2.2.4.3.7.3h11c.3 0 .5-.1.7-.3.2-.2.3-.5.3-.7s-.1-.5-.3-.7zM5.8 14.7l6.2 6.3 6.2-6.3c.2-.2.3-.5.3-.7s-.1-.5-.3-.7c-.2-.2-.4-.3-.7-.3h-11c-.3 0-.5.1-.7.3-.2.2-.3.5-.3.7s.1.5.3.7z\"\/><\/svg><\/span><\/span><\/span><\/a><\/span><\/div>\n<nav><ul class='ez-toc-list ez-toc-list-level-1 ' ><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-1\" href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/blogs\/complete-list-of-ba-subjects\/#What_is_a_BA_Degree\" >What is a BA Degree<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-2\" href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/blogs\/complete-list-of-ba-subjects\/#Why_should_one_do_a_BA_Degree\" >Why should one do a BA Degree?&nbsp;<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-3\" href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/blogs\/complete-list-of-ba-subjects\/#Types_of_BA_Courses\" >Types of BA Courses&nbsp;<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-4\" href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/blogs\/complete-list-of-ba-subjects\/#BA_Subject_List_with_Duration\" >BA Subject List with Duration&nbsp;<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-5\" href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/blogs\/complete-list-of-ba-subjects\/#Top_3_Popular_BA_Subjects_with_Reasons\" >Top 3 Popular BA Subjects with Reasons&nbsp;<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-6\" href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/blogs\/complete-list-of-ba-subjects\/#Online_Bachelor_of_Arts_Syllabus_by_Sikkim_Manipal_University\" >Online Bachelor of Arts Syllabus by Sikkim Manipal University.&nbsp;<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-7\" href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/blogs\/complete-list-of-ba-subjects\/#Admission_Requirements_for_BA_Degree\" >Admission Requirements for BA Degree&nbsp;<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-8\" href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/blogs\/complete-list-of-ba-subjects\/#Career_Prospects_After_BA_Degree\" >Career Prospects After BA Degree&nbsp;<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-9\" href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/blogs\/complete-list-of-ba-subjects\/#Tips_for_Choosing_the_Right_BA_Specialization\" >Tips for Choosing the Right BA Specialization&nbsp;<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-10\" href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/blogs\/complete-list-of-ba-subjects\/#How_will_an_online_BA_from_SMU_help_your_career\" >How will an online BA from SMU help your career?&nbsp;<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-11\" href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/blogs\/complete-list-of-ba-subjects\/#Conclusion\" >Conclusion&nbsp;<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-12\" href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/blogs\/complete-list-of-ba-subjects\/#FAQs\" >FAQs&nbsp;<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-13\" href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/blogs\/complete-list-of-ba-subjects\/#References\" >References<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/nav><\/div>\n\n<p><em>According to a Times of India survey, more than 78.9% of 4.1 crore higher education students are enrolled at the undergraduate level, and more than one crore of those students are pursuing a BA.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/em>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>These insights highlight the reality check of today\u2019s education system: BA degree is the gateway to landing versatile career opportunities of your choice. Additionally, unlike other courses, BA subjects help students to develop critical thinking, writing, and communication skills, which is widely endorsed in all lines of work.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>At its core, BA course sets the tone and the foundation for advanced study for students to carve out a wonderful profession out of it. But what exactly does it entail? What are the further details of this course? How to get started? Which is the right stream for you?&nbsp;&nbsp;This blog will reflect on all the above questions and give a comprehensive understanding of the BA subject list.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"What_is_a_BA_Degree\"><\/span><strong>What is a BA Degree<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The BA, or Bachelor of Arts, is a three-year undergraduate program that emphasizes many academic disciplines. There are six semesters in all. Students are exposed to a wide range of subjects in BA, allowing them to comprehend the vast span of this stream.\u00a0\u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>In the initial year of their Bachelor of Arts (BA) program students typically engage in a broad spectrum of general subjects to establish a comprehensive academic foundation. Courses often include English literature, history, political science, and a language elective. These subjects serve as a fundamental exploration into diverse disciplines, fostering critical thinking skills, effective communication, and cultural sensitivity.\u00a0\u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>As students&#8217; progress through their academic journey, the curriculum evolves to encompass more specialized, or core subjects aligned with their chosen major or area of concentration. This strategic progression ensures a well-rounded education, equipping students with a diverse skill set and a nuanced understanding of various fields within the arts and humanities.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Also Read: <a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/blogs\/ba-economics-vs-ba-political-science\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"><strong>BA Economics vs BA Political Science<\/strong><\/a>\u00a0<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Why_should_one_do_a_BA_Degree\"><\/span><strong>Why should one do a BA Degree?<\/strong>&nbsp;<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Being one of the simpler and more promising degrees to complete, several students choose this course to explore new opportunities. Apart from that, below are some of the reasons to choose a BA degree.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Job opportunities in both public and private sector<\/strong>: Once the BA course is completed, students can look for jobs in both private and public sector.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Provide with transferable skills<\/strong>: With a completed BA degree, students attain skills such as communication, leadership, time management, problem-solving and many more.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Assist in intellectual exploration<\/strong>: It gives students a purpose-driven curriculum in the subjects they are passionate about and helps them understand it in detail.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Develops a broad worldview: <\/strong>Encourages cultural awareness, empathy, and a profound insight into society.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Promotes creativity and independent thought<\/strong>: Focusses on innovation and individual perspectives in problem-solving.&nbsp;<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Valued in the job market: <\/strong>Employers appreciate BA graduates for their soft skills and ability to adapt.&nbsp;<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Also Read: <\/strong><a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/blogs\/why-choose-ba-after-12th-arts\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"><strong>Why choose BA after 12th arts?<\/strong><\/a><strong><\/strong>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Types_of_BA_Courses\"><\/span><strong>Types of BA Courses<\/strong>&nbsp;<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Over the years, the BA course has evolved and branched out into different types based on academic interests, career goals, and learning preferences. Below are the five major types of BA courses that students can choose from:&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>1. General BA&nbsp;<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>A General BA is a traditional UG program that offers an extensive and balanced education in humanities, languages, and social sciences. It does not emphasize a single subject in-depth but enables students to explore multiple disciplines, often with a combination of electives and core courses.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>2. BA (Hons.)<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Students can now take up <a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/online-bba-honors-mahe\"><strong>Online BA Honours<\/strong><\/a> which is just like the traditional BA but focus on one core subject with advanced coursework. This will sometimes also include a research project or thesis in the last semester providing higher academic standard than the general BA.\u00a0\u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>3. Vocational BA<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Vocational BA is nothing but a culmination of academic learning and expertise in job-ready skills such as journalism, hospitality, tourism, event management, or social work. They consist of several industry-oriented insights, various internships, applied training, and so on.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>4. Integrated BA Programs<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Students who are looking forward to completing their undergraduate degree with a postgraduate or professional online degree in a single streamlined course, then integrated BA programs work the best in their favor. This is a great time saver, and learners are equipped with multiple specializations. Some common examples are BA+MA, BA+ B.Ed., BA+LLB and so on.\u00a0\u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>5. Online BA<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>With the evolution of technology, learning is possible pretty much from anywhere. Online BA helps students provide the flexibility they need to balance both their education and career. Being one of the most preferred types, online BA is more affordable and takes the learners through self-paced learning.\u00a0\u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Also Read: <\/strong><a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/blogs\/regular-vs-distance-vs-online-ba\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"><strong>Regular BA vs distance BA vs online BA<\/strong><\/a><strong><\/strong>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"BA_Subject_List_with_Duration\"><\/span><strong>BA Subject List with Duration<\/strong>&nbsp;<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>BA courses have UG programs in Humanities, Sociology, English and so on. They are classified as academic, practical or career oriented based on the core subjects they are dealing with. This results in varying durations for the completion of each course. Below is the complete guide of the different BA programs along with the BA subjects and their duration.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table><thead><tr><th><strong>BA Programs<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/th><th><strong>Core Subjects<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/th><th><strong>Duration<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/th><\/tr><\/thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>BA in English<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/td><td>Literature, Linguistics, Literary Criticism, Drama, Postcolonial Literature&nbsp;<\/td><td>3 years&nbsp;<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><strong>BA in History<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/td><td>Indian History, World History, Historiography, Archaeology, Modern Asia&nbsp;<\/td><td>3 years&nbsp;<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><strong>BA in Political Science<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/td><td>Indian Politics, Comparative Politics, International Relations, Political Theory&nbsp;<\/td><td>3 years&nbsp;<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><strong>BA in Sociology<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/td><td>Social Institutions, Indian Society, Gender &amp; Society, Social Change, Research Methods&nbsp;<\/td><td>3 years&nbsp;<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><strong>BA in Psychology<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/td><td>Social Psychology, Developmental Psychology, Abnormal Psychology, Testing, Counseling&nbsp;<\/td><td>3 years&nbsp;<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><strong>BA in Geography<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/td><td>Physical &amp; Human Geography, Climatology, Cartography, Economic Geography&nbsp;<\/td><td>3 years&nbsp;<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><strong>BA in Philosophy<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/td><td>Indian &amp; Western Philosophy, Logic, Ethics, Religion, Metaphysics&nbsp;<\/td><td>3 years&nbsp;<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><strong>BA in Economics<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/td><td>Microeconomics, Macroeconomics, Public Finance, Indian Economy, International Economics&nbsp;<\/td><td>3 years&nbsp;<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><strong>BA in Journalism &amp; Mass Comm.<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/td><td>Reporting, Editing, Media Ethics, Public Relations, Digital Journalism&nbsp;<\/td><td>3 years&nbsp;<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><strong>BA in Fine Arts<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/td><td>Drawing, Painting, Sculpture, Art History, Aesthetics&nbsp;<\/td><td>3\u20134 years&nbsp;<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><strong>BA in Performing Arts<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/td><td>Dance\/Music\/Theatre, Stagecraft, Indian Aesthetics, Performance Techniques&nbsp;<\/td><td>3 years&nbsp;<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><strong>BA in International Relations<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/td><td>Global Politics, Diplomacy, Foreign Policy, Security Studies, International Law&nbsp;<\/td><td>3 years&nbsp;<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><strong>BA in Public Administration<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/td><td>Public Policy, Governance, Indian Administration, Financial &amp; Personnel Administration&nbsp;<\/td><td>3 years&nbsp;<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><strong>BA in Anthropology<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/td><td>Cultural Anthropology, Physical Anthropology, Ethnography, Archaeology&nbsp;<\/td><td>3 years&nbsp;<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><strong>BA in Education<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/td><td>Educational Psychology, Curriculum Studies, Pedagogy, Teaching Methods&nbsp;<\/td><td>3 years&nbsp;<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><strong>BA LLB (Integrated)<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/td><td>Law (IPC, Constitutional Law, Family Law), Political Science, Sociology, Legal Writing&nbsp;<\/td><td>5 years&nbsp;<\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Also Read: <\/strong><a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/blogs\/how-to-choose-the-right-online-ba-program\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"><strong>How to choose the right online BA program for a bright future<\/strong><\/a><strong><\/strong>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Top_3_Popular_BA_Subjects_with_Reasons\"><\/span><strong>Top 3 Popular BA Subjects with Reasons<\/strong>&nbsp;<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>As per close observation and many convincing reasons, the below three are the most chosen BA subjects by graduates.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>BA in English<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>BA English is one of the most preferred BA programs by students as they can help them land jobs in teaching, content writing, media, publishing, and digital marketing. It helps students to develop their communication skills, critical thinking and so on.\u00a0\u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>BA in Political Science<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Students who are looking forward to having a future in civil services, government jobs, or careers in international relations or law prefer a BA in political science. This degree will help them have a stronger perspective into public policy, law and order, the judicial system and so on which will also pave way for the UPSC or other competitive exams.\u00a0\u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>BA in<\/strong> <strong>Psychology<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>With mental health being a priority nowadays, students can take up a BA degree in psychology, if they are looking to build a career in therapy, social work, counseling and so on. Further, they can also go for a higher study in courses like behavioral sciences, MSW and so on.\u00a0\u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Also Read: <\/strong><a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/blogs\/top-ba-specializations-to-choose\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"><strong>In-demand BA specializations to pursue<\/strong><\/a><strong><\/strong>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Online_Bachelor_of_Arts_Syllabus_by_Sikkim_Manipal_University\"><\/span><strong>Online Bachelor of Arts Syllabus by Sikkim Manipal University<\/strong>.&nbsp;<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Here is the complete list of BA subjects semester wise offered by<strong> <\/strong><a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/institution\/sikkim-manipal-university\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"><strong>Sikkim Manipal University<\/strong><\/a>.\u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Online BA English Curriculum&nbsp;<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table><thead><tr><th>Semester 1 Subjects<\/th><th>Semester 2 Subjects<\/th><th>Semester 3 Subjects<\/th><th>Semester 4 Subjects<\/th><th>Semester 5 Subjects<\/th><th>Semester 6 Subjects<\/th><\/tr><\/thead><tbody><tr><td>Indian English Literature<\/td><td>World Literature<\/td><td>Essays and Poetry<\/td><td>New Literature in English<\/td><td>Victorian and Modern Literature<\/td><td>American Literature<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Communicative English<\/td><td>Functional English<\/td><td>Universal Human Values<\/td><td>Literary Terms, Forms, and Movements<\/td><td>Poetry: Evolution, Elements and Genres<\/td><td>One Act Plays: Introduction &amp; Studies<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Foundations of Political Science<\/td><td>Political Theory<\/td><td>Comparative Political Analysis<\/td><td>Women Writing in English<\/td><td>Children\u2019s Literature<\/td><td>Novels and Short Stories<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Introduction to Sociology<\/td><td>Sociology in India<\/td><td>Rural Sociology<\/td><td>Classical Indian Political Thought<\/td><td>Human Rights<\/td><td>United Nations and Global Conflicts<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Natural Science<\/td><td>Environmental Studies<\/td><td>Digital Fluency<\/td><td>Urban Sociology<\/td><td>Social Problems in India<\/td><td>Sociology of Change and Development<\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Online BA Sociology Curriculum&nbsp;<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table><thead><tr><th>Semester 1 Subjects<\/th><th>Semester 2 Subjects<\/th><th>Semester 3 Subjects<\/th><th>Semester 4 Subjects<\/th><th>Semester 5 Subjects<\/th><th>Semester 6 Subjects<\/th><\/tr><\/thead><tbody><tr><td>Introduction to Sociology<\/td><td>Sociology in India<\/td><td>Rural Sociology<\/td><td>Urban Sociology<\/td><td>Classical Sociological Thinkers<\/td><td>Sociology of Change and Development<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Foundations of Political Science<\/td><td>Political Theory<\/td><td>Comparative Political Analysis<\/td><td>Family, Kinship, and Marriage<\/td><td>Social Problems in India<\/td><td>Sociology of Education<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Indian English Literature<\/td><td>World Literature<\/td><td>Essays and Poetry<\/td><td>Principle of Sociology<\/td><td>Social Demography<\/td><td>Social Movements in India<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Communicative English<\/td><td>Functional English<\/td><td>Universal Human Values<\/td><td>Classical Indian Political Thought<\/td><td>Human Rights<\/td><td>United Nations and Global Conflicts<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Natural Science<\/td><td>Environmental Studies<\/td><td>Digital Fluency<\/td><td>New Literature in English<\/td><td>Children\u2019s Literature<\/td><td>American Literature<\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Online BA Political Science Curriculum&nbsp;<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table><thead><tr><th>Semester 1 Subjects<\/th><th>Semester 2 Subjects<\/th><th>Semester 3 Subjects<\/th><th>Semester 4 Subjects<\/th><th>Semester 5 Subjects<\/th><th>Semester 6 Subjects<\/th><\/tr><\/thead><tbody><tr><td>Foundations of Political Science<\/td><td>Political Theory<\/td><td>Comparative Political Analysis<\/td><td>Classical Indian Political Thought<\/td><td>Political Processes in India<\/td><td>United Nations and Global Conflicts<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Introduction to Sociology<\/td><td>Sociology in India<\/td><td>Rural Sociology<\/td><td>Theories of International Relations<\/td><td>India\u2019s Foreign Policy in a Globalized World<\/td><td>Public Policy and Administration in India<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Indian English Literature<\/td><td>World Literature<\/td><td>Essays and Poetry<\/td><td>Political Economy<\/td><td>Human Rights<\/td><td>Gender and Politics<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Communicative English<\/td><td>Functional English<\/td><td>Universal Human Values<\/td><td>Urban Sociology<\/td><td>Social Problems in India<\/td><td>Sociology of Change and Development<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Natural Science<\/td><td>Environmental Studies<\/td><td>Digital Fluency<\/td><td>New Literature in English<\/td><td>Children\u2019s Literature<\/td><td>American Literature<\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Admission_Requirements_for_BA_Degree\"><\/span><strong>Admission Requirements for BA Degree<\/strong>&nbsp;<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Requirements for BA programs may vary by institution, but generally include:&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>10+2 or equivalent:<\/strong> Minimum academic qualifications are necessary.&nbsp;<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Standardized tests:<\/strong> Some institutions may require standardized tests like the CUET.&nbsp;<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Career_Prospects_After_BA_Degree\"><\/span><strong>Career Prospects After BA Degree<\/strong>&nbsp;<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>BA comes with a multitude of opportunities when it comes to career choices. Below are some of the most common options that learners can look forward to:&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Civil Services &amp; Government Jobs<\/strong>: BA graduates can attend UPSC, SSC, and state-level exams to secure a prestigious position in the government sector.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Education Sector<\/strong>: With an extra B.Ed. or an MA+NET., graduates can take up teaching positions in schools or colleges if that is what drives their passion.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Media, Journalism &amp; Communication<\/strong>: Another interesting option students can take up after BA is PR, journalism, digital marketing, content writing and so on.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Corporate &amp; Business Roles<\/strong>: Students with good people and communication skills can opt for roles in HR, business development and so on.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Law and Legal Services<\/strong>: With an integrated LLB degree, graduates can take up professional roles such as paralegals, legal advisors, lawyers and so on.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Psychology &amp; Counseling<\/strong>: After completion of BA in Psychology students can take up roles like school counselor, mental health worker, or career coach.&nbsp;<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>NGOs &amp; Social Work<\/strong>: Working in NGOs as social workers, program officers, or community outreach professionals is another good option after completing BA.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Creative &amp; Arts Careers<\/strong>: BA in Fine Arts or Performing Arts can lead to roles in acting, drama, theatre, or music.&nbsp;<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Travel, Tourism &amp; Hospitality<\/strong>: Travel consultant, tour manager, or hotel executive are some options for people who are inclined towards tourism and looking for a career after completing their BA in tourism.&nbsp;<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Higher Education &amp; Specializations<\/strong>: Pursuing postgrad studies like MA, MBA, or MSW enhances expertise and opens specialized career paths.&nbsp;<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Read More: <\/strong><a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/blogs\/diverse-industries-after-online-ba-degree\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"><strong>Diverse industries you can work for after a BA degree<\/strong><\/a><strong><\/strong>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Tips_for_Choosing_the_Right_BA_Specialization\"><\/span><strong>Tips for Choosing the Right BA Specialization<\/strong>&nbsp;<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Assess Your Interests<\/strong>&nbsp;<br>Choose a field you\u2019re genuinely curious and passionate about as this keeps you motivated throughout the course.&nbsp;<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Evaluate Career Goals<\/strong>&nbsp;<br>Think about your long-term professional goals and pick a specialization aligned with potential career paths (e.g., Journalism, Psychology, English).&nbsp;<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Research Job Opportunities<\/strong>&nbsp;<br>Explore what kind of roles and industries are linked to each specialization and their current demand in the job market.&nbsp;<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Consider Higher Education Plans<\/strong>&nbsp;<br>If you\u2019re planning to pursue further studies (like MA, LLB, MBA), choose a BA specialization that provides a solid foundation for it.&nbsp;<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Understand the Curriculum<\/strong>&nbsp;<br>Go through the course structure and subjects to ensure they match your learning preferences and academic strengths.&nbsp;<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Seek Guidance<\/strong>&nbsp;<br>Talk to career counselors, alumni, or current students for first-hand insights about the course and its scope.&nbsp;<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Think Global and Local<\/strong>&nbsp;<br>Consider both local job trends and global relevance if you plan to work or study abroad.&nbsp;<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Check College Strengths<\/strong>&nbsp;<br>Choose a specialization that the college is known for\u2014better faculty and facilities often mean a richer learning experience.&nbsp;<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Stay Open-Minded<\/strong>&nbsp;<br>If undecided, start with a general BA and narrow down your interests in the first year based on experience and exposure.&nbsp;<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"How_will_an_online_BA_from_SMU_help_your_career\"><\/span><strong>How will an online BA from SMU help your career?<\/strong>&nbsp;<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>A reputable university\u2019s online BA program, like the one offered by SMU, has various benefits for you as it helps to enhance your career. This Sikkim Manipal University (SMU) online Bachelor of Arts (BA) with a blend of English, Sociology, and Political Science is created for students wishing to build competency in different fields &amp; disciplines to succeed in the fast-paced world. Over three years, there are six semesters in this UGC-recognised program.\u00a0\u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Read More: <\/strong><a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/blogs\/pros-and-cons-of-online-ba-for-working-professionals\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"><strong>Pros and cons of online BA for working professionals<\/strong><\/a><strong><\/strong>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Students will receive in-depth knowledge and skills in English literature, political science, and sociology through this program, and they may explore professional prospects that are in line with their interests and academic specialties. A critical step in determining your academic career is figuring out the BA course selections. You are given the opportunity to study specialized fields, develop key abilities, and explore the core subjects for your BA second and third year, thanks to this procedure.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>You will graduate from our online BA program with the skills and knowledge needed to launch a successful career in a variety of employment sectors.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Conclusion\"><\/span><strong>Conclusion<\/strong>&nbsp;<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>In conclusion, the journey through a Bachelor of Arts (BA) program is a dynamic and transformative expedition spanning three distinctive years. The carefully curated subject lists in the first year lay the groundwork, fostering foundational knowledge, critical thinking, and a broad understanding of various disciplines. As students&#8217; progress into the subsequent years, the subject lists evolve, offering a nuanced exploration of their chosen major or concentration.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The second and third years of the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/online-ba-degree-smu\"><strong>online BA program<\/strong><\/a> delve deeper into specialized subjects, honing expertise and refining skills, culminating in a comprehensive and well-rounded academic experience. This progressive structure not only encourages intellectual growth and personal development but also empowers students to navigate the complexities of their chosen fields with depth and proficiency. The three-year BA subject list, collectively, epitomizes the essence of a holistic education\u2014imbuing students with a wealth of knowledge, fostering interdisciplinary connections, and preparing them for a future of continual learning and meaningful contributions in their chosen fields.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"FAQs\"><\/span><strong>FAQs<\/strong>&nbsp;<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>1. How many subjects are there in BA 1<sup>st<\/sup> year?&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>There are 6 subjects in 1<sup>st<\/sup> year BA.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>2. Is BA a 3-year course?<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>BA is a 3-year course with 6 semesters.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>3. What is the salary of a BA graduate?<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>&nbsp;BA graduates can expect 2-5LPA to get paid in the first year. It also depends on their work experience and skill set.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>4. Is BA a 4-year course?<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>BA can now be a 4-year course in India, depending on the university and whether it has implemented NEP 2020.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>5. What are the 5 compulsory subjects in BA?<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The five compulsory subjects of BA are:&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>English (Language)&nbsp;<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>History&nbsp;<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Political Science&nbsp;<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Sociology&nbsp;<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Environmental Studies (compulsory)<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Foundation Course (sometimes)&nbsp;<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>6. Is BA easy to pass?<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>BA is not a technical course and most of the core subjects are passion driven. With the right university, mentors and curriculum, BA is a relatively easy to pass degree.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>7. Is BA a good career option?<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Yes. BA opens doors for several career options in multi-disciplinary fields.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>8. Can I do MBA after BA?<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Yes. You can do an MBA after a BA.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>9. What are the job profiles after BA?<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Below are some of the career choices graduates can pursue after BA&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Journalism&nbsp;<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Education&nbsp;<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Public Relations<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Human Resources<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Social Work&nbsp;<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Civil Services&nbsp;<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Marketing&nbsp;<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Content Writing&nbsp;<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Law&nbsp;<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Research&nbsp;<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>10. Which is the best BA or BSc?<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Both courses are good. It depends on the learner&#8217;s interest and career aspirations. Students who are looking for a more technical course can opt for a BSc and learners inclined towards arts and literature can go for a BA course. &nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>11. What are the types of BA courses?<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The main different forms of BA course are:&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>General BA&nbsp;<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>BA (Hons.)&nbsp;<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Vocational BA<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Integrated BA Programs<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Online BA&nbsp;<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>12. What are the eligibility criteria for BA?&nbsp;<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Candidates must have completed 10+2 from a recognized national or state board institution or 10+3 diploma from a recognized national or state institute.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"References\"><\/span>References<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/timesofindia.indiatimes.com\/india\/1\/3rd-of-undergraduate-students-in-india-doing-ba-survey\/articleshow\/97465229.cms?from=mdr\">https:\/\/timesofindia.indiatimes.com\/india\/1\/3rd-of-undergraduate-students-in-india-doing-ba-survey\/articleshow\/97465229.cms?from=mdr<\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>According to a Times of India survey, more than 78.9% of 4.1 crore higher education students are enrolled at the undergraduate level, and more than one crore of those students are pursuing a BA.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; These insights highlight the reality check of today\u2019s education system: BA degree is the gateway to landing versatile career opportunities of [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":126,"featured_media":680420,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"_acf_changed":false,"footnotes":""},"categories":[609],"tags":[219,19,220],"class_list":["post-680414","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","category-bachelor-of-arts","tag-online-bachelor-of-arts","tag-online-degree","tag-sikkim-manipal-university"],"yoast_head":"<!-- This site is optimized with the Yoast SEO plugin v27.5 - https:\/\/yoast.com\/product\/yoast-seo-wordpress\/ -->\n<title>Guide to BA Degree Courses: Subject List, Specialization<\/title>\n<meta name=\"description\" content=\"Get a glimpse of the wide range of subjects in a Bachelor of Arts (BA) program. Explore English literature, history, sociology, and more.\" \/>\n<meta name=\"robots\" content=\"index, follow, max-snippet:-1, max-image-preview:large, max-video-preview:-1\" \/>\n<link rel=\"canonical\" href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/680414\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:locale\" content=\"en_GB\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:type\" content=\"article\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:title\" content=\"Guide to BA Degree Courses: Subject List, Specialization\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:description\" content=\"Get a glimpse of the wide range of subjects in a Bachelor of Arts (BA) program. Explore English literature, history, sociology, and more.\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:url\" content=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/blogs\/complete-list-of-ba-subjects\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:site_name\" content=\"Online Manipal\" \/>\n<meta property=\"article:publisher\" content=\"https:\/\/www.facebook.com\/onlinemanipal\" \/>\n<meta property=\"article:published_time\" content=\"2025-05-12T11:20:30+00:00\" \/>\n<meta property=\"article:modified_time\" content=\"2025-11-24T13:06:26+00:00\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:image\" content=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Subject-list-in-BA-first-year.jpg\" \/>\n\t<meta property=\"og:image:width\" content=\"701\" \/>\n\t<meta property=\"og:image:height\" content=\"395\" \/>\n\t<meta property=\"og:image:type\" content=\"image\/jpeg\" \/>\n<meta name=\"author\" content=\"Krishnanjali KU\" \/>\n<meta name=\"twitter:card\" content=\"summary_large_image\" \/>\n<meta name=\"twitter:label1\" content=\"Written by\" \/>\n\t<meta name=\"twitter:data1\" content=\"Krishnanjali KU\" \/>\n\t<meta name=\"twitter:label2\" content=\"Estimated reading time\" \/>\n\t<meta name=\"twitter:data2\" content=\"14 minutes\" \/>\n<script type=\"application\/ld+json\" class=\"yoast-schema-graph\">{\"@context\":\"https:\\\/\\\/schema.org\",\"@graph\":[{\"@type\":\"WebPage\",\"@id\":\"https:\\\/\\\/www.onlinemanipal.co